marked: Impulse control disorders (ICDs) and related behaviours commonly occur in Parkinson disease (PD),
Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson’s disease (QUIP)-short form

For the change in DAT availability from baseline to 1 year, our analysis of the full cohort suggested that a greater decrease in right caudate binding is associated with an increased risk of incident ICD symptoms

In the DRT subgroup only, a greater decrease in right caudate (OR=4.03 (1.39 to 11.68), p=0.01) and total mean striatal (OR=6.90 (1.09 to 43.50), p=0.04) binding was significantly associated with increased risk of incident ICD symptoms.
In the full cohort, lower right
putamen DAT binding ratios at a given postbaseline visit were associated with a higher risk of incident ICD symptoms at that visit.
